Title: I Need Not Speak
---
The Lord touched my mouth
and spoke.

Without sound my Lord
filled me.

I had chattered, my
heart spun,

Words flying, birds in-
to air.

But that touch to my
mouth stopped

God's going out, and
now my

Lord -- I can hear you
inside.
